          {
            "spell": "w",
            "id": "skill-lvl2w-template",
            "level": 2,
            "reason": "With an extra dash from your <ScAbilityInline_v2 spellKey=\"W\" />, you can initiate trades more aggressively. Prepare <ScRuneInline runeIdentifier=\"Grasp of the Undying\" /> like we did before.&#x20;\\n\\n* <ScComboInline steps={[\"W\", \"Dash in if you need distance\", \"Q1\", \"Dash\", \"AA\", \"Q2\", \"Dash out\"]} />\\n* There's also a 50% increase in <ScAbilityInline_v2 spellKey=\"W\" possessive />'s damage portion if you successfully use it to tank enemy champion damage, so it's optimal to start this type of trade by blocking some damage with your <ScAbilityInline_v2 spellKey=\"W\" />, but isn't required.",
            "title": "Shields Have Teeth"
          },
          {
            "reason": "$23",
            "level": 3,
            "id": "skill-lvl3e-template",
            "title": "Hit and Run Combo",
            "spell": "e"
          },
          {
            "spell": "r",
            "id": "skill-lvl6r-template",
            "reason": "$24",
            "level": 6,
            "title": "R Is Overtuned, Abuse It"
          },
          {
            "spell": "q",
            "level": 9,
            "reason": "At level 9, you finally have max rank <ScAbilityInline_v2 spellKey=\"Q\" />. Around this time, you'll usually have <ScItemInline itemName=\"Eclipse\" /> as well, which has a 6 second cooldown on its shield, synergizing perfectly with <ScChampionInline championId=\"Ambessa\" />'s short <ScAbilityInline_v2 spellKey=\"Q\" /> cooldown.&#x20;\\n\\n* Look to proc <ScItemInline itemName=\"Eclipse\" /> as much as possible, and use <ScAbilityInline_v2 spellKey=\"W\" /> when you need extra shielding or want to all-in.\\n* At this point, <ScChampionInline championId=\"Ambessa\" /> does not lose statchecks to 90% of champions - if you still feel like your matchup is still rough, use the <ScItemInline itemName=\"Eclipse\" /> + <ScAbilityInline_v2 spellKey=\"W\" /> shielding to poke them down in short trades, then go for an all-in with your <ScAbilityInline_v2 spellKey=\"R\" /> when they're low enough.",
            "id": "skill-lvl9q-atlast",
            "title": "90% Can't Beat You"
          }
